      • getValues

        public ValueList getValues(PExp exp,
                           ObjectContext ctxt)
        Return a list of all the updatable values read by the expression. This is used to add listeners to values that affect permission guards, so that the guard may be efficiently re-evaluated when the values change.
        Parameters:
        exp -
        ctxt - The context in which to search for values.
        Returns:
        A list of values read by the expression.

      • findExpression

        public PExp findExpression(PExp exp,
                           int lineno)
        Find an expression starting on the given line. Single expressions just compare their location to lineno, but expressions with sub-expressions iterate over their branches.
        Parameters:
        exp -
        lineno - The line number to locate.
        Returns:
        An expression starting on the line, or null.
